{"type":"message","id":"a793a9be","parentId":"7ce3d95c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:58:10.417Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7quumalf9iyg_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 115700\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: a (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. CFI analysis is complete - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n2. Next action is to run CFI-weighted compression experiment comparing next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Using CFI scores to weight invariants instead of just frequency\r\n2. Comparing prediction quality\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the invariants data\r\n2. Applies CFI weighting to compress\r\n3. Compares against frequency-only baseline\r\n4. Measures prediction quality\r\n\r\nThe experiment should test whether CFI-weighted compression gives better next-pulse prediction than frequency-based compression.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist:\r\n- research/CFI_RESULTS.md - has the analysis\r\n- research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\n- research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\n\r\nI should create a new file: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md or a script to run this experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, let me create the experiment specification first, then maybe run it. But wait - I don't have code execution ability, just file editing. So I should create a document or script that outlines/automates the experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create an experiment design document that specifies:\r\n1. The methodology\r\n2. How to run it\r\n3. Expected outcomes\r\n\r\nOr I could create a script that would run this comparison.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0). The next logical step is to test whether CFI-weighted compression outperforms frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment specification that defines the comparison methodology between CFI-weighted and frequency-baseline approaches, setting up the framework for the actual experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nCompare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency-baseline for next-pulse prediction quality.\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression preserves causal anchors (high CFI) while filtering metaprogramming noise (CFI=0), yielding better prediction than frequency-only compression.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Dataset\r\n- Source: Session invariants from `state/sessions/` \r\n- Filter: Only sessions with contiguous pulses (to ensure prediction is meaningful)\r\n\r\n### Two Compression Methods\r\n\r\n**Method A: Frequency-Baseline (current)**\r\n```\r\nweight = frequency / max_frequency\r\n```\r\n- Ignores CFI entirely\r\n- Treats all invariants equally by normalization\r\n\r\n**Method B: CFI-Weighted (proposed)**\r\n```\r\nweight = (CFI^�) * (frequency / max_frequency)^(1-�)\r\n```\r\n- � = 0.7 (CFI dominance, tunable)\r\n- CFI=0 invariants receive near-zero weight\r\n- CFI>0.7 invariants preserved at high weight\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Prediction Quality\r\n1. For each session S, withhold final pulse P_n\r\n2. Compress invariants from pulses P_1...P_{n-1} using each method\r\n3. Generate prediction for P_n\r\n4. Score prediction against actual P_n (BLEU, semantic similarity, or invariant overlap)\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n| Metric | Frequency-Baseline | CFI-Weighted | Improvement |\r\n|--------|-------------------|--------------|-------------|\r\n| Invariant overlap | baseline | higher | +15-30% |\r\n| Semantic coherence | baseline | higher | +10-20% |\r\n| Noise ratio | ~45% | ~10% | -35pp |\r\n\r\n## Implementation Steps\r\n1. Extract pulse sequences from sessions\r\n2. Compute CFI for each invariant (already done in CFI_RESULTS.md)\r\n3. Implement both weighting schemes\r\n4. Run withheld-pulse prediction across all eligible sessions\r\n5. Compute aggregate metrics\r\n\r\n## Files Needed\r\n- `state/sessions/` - pulse sequences\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - CFI scores per invariant\r\n- Script: `experiments/cfi_compression_test.py` (to be created)\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n- [x] Hypothesis defined\r\n- [ ] Script implemented\r\n- [ ] Experiment run\r\n- [ ] Results analyzed\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:57:30"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":927,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 115700\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: a (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. CFI analysis is complete - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n2. Next action is to run CFI-weighted compression experiment comparing next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Using CFI scores to weight invariants instead of just frequency\r\n2. Comparing prediction quality\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the invariants data\r\n2. Applies CFI weighting to compress\r\n3. Compares against frequency-only baseline\r\n4. Measures prediction quality\r\n\r\nThe experiment should test whether CFI-weighted compression gives better next-pulse prediction than frequ