irely\r\n- Treats all invariants equally by normalization\r\n\r\n**Method B: CFI-Weighted (proposed)**\r\n```\r\nweight = (CFI^�) * (frequency / max_frequency)^(1-�)\r\n```\r\n- � = 0.7 (CFI dominance, tunable)\r\n- CFI=0 invariants receive near-zero weight\r\n- CFI>0.7 invariants preserved at high weight\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Prediction Quality\r\n1. For each session S, withhold final pulse P_n\r\n2. Compress invariants from pulses P_1...P_{n-1} using each method\r\n3. Generate prediction for P_n\r\n4. Score prediction against actual P_n (BLEU, semantic similarity, or invariant overlap)\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n| Metric | Frequency-Baseline | CFI-Weighted | Improvement |\r\n|--------|-------------------|--------------|-------------|\r\n| Invariant overlap | baseline | higher | +15-30% |\r\n| Semantic coherence | baseline | higher | +10-20% |\r\n| Noise ratio | ~45% | ~10% | -35pp |\r\n\r\n## Implementation Steps\r\n1. Extract pulse sequences from sessions\r\n2. Compute CFI for each invariant (already done in CFI_RESULTS.md)\r\n3. Implement both weighting schemes\r\n4. Run withheld-pulse prediction across all eligible sessions\r\n5. Compute aggregate metrics\r\n\r\n## Files Needed\r\n- `state/sessions/` - pulse sequences\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - CFI scores per invariant\r\n- Script: `experiments/cfi_compression_test.py` (to be created)\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n- [x] Hypothesis defined\r\n- [ ] Script implemented\r\n- [ ] Experiment run\r\n- [ ] Results analyzed\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:57:30","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774367890414}}
